          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>Richmond</placeName>
                                        <date>Mar. 6th 1852</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Esteemed Friend!</p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)">Hoping you ar-<lb/>rived safe and met your
                                        imme<lb/>diate friends in usual health as<lb/> I trust you
                                        enjoy, I wish you<lb/> a happy and merry
                                                  <date><sic>Pureem</sic></date> hoping<lb/> you may
                                        live many more years<lb/> to see its return,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">We are all well, I neglec-<lb/>ted when you were
                                        here for<lb/> to request you to send me the<lb/> various
                                        forms of blanks now<lb/> in use in the <add>?</add> in
                                        your<lb/> city. we wish to adopt the same<lb/> here, so
                                        please by return of the<lb/> mail send them to me, I
                                        mean<lb/> the various notices &amp;c,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">All the families join in kind<lb/> remembrance to
                                        you, I regret that<lb/> you could not remain here
                                        longer,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mr Henry</persName> arrived here the
                                        day<lb/> after you left, called on <persName>Mr Jacob<lb/>
                                                  A. Levy</persName>, who did not request him<lb/>
                                        to remain and deliver a lecture<lb/> in synagogue, so he
                                        left the fol</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>lowing morning for the <placeName>North</placeName>,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Here has nothing new transpired<lb/> since you
                                        left, I hope that du-<lb/>ring the summer you will come<lb/>
                                        on and spend some time with us<lb/> really I cannot call
                                        your short<lb/> stay more than a Doctors visit</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Love to <persName>Aunt Sally</persName> and<lb/>
                                        my dear sister and family,<lb/> to my old friend
                                                  <persName>Mrs hart</persName><lb/> and believe me
                                        to remain as<lb/> ever  Yours truly</p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)">
                                        <persName role="author">Jacob Ezekiel</persName>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">
                                        <placeName>Pa</placeName>
                              </p>
